 rapher Rania Matar (b. 1964\, Lebanon)\, whose striking portraits documen
 t young women persisting in uncertain times. Matar's lens highlights wome
 n's creativity\, strength\, dignity\, and resilienceŌĆöoffering a powerfu
 l counter-narrative to the challenges of her country and region. <a href=
 "https://artmuseum.indiana.edu/exhibitions/upcoming/_feature-exhibitions/
 2026-03-05-rania-matar-where-do-i-go.html">Read more about this featured 
